{
  "texts": [
    "By analyzing these AST graphs, researchers can evaluate the performance of GNNs in tasks such as code classification and defect detection.",
    "The PCQM4Mv2 (Hu et al. 2103b) is a quantum chemistry dataset designed to predict an important molecular property of a given molecule, which is important for understanding the quantum behavior of molecules, designing novel materials and drugs, and so on.",
    "In addition to the three main dataset collections mentioned above, several other datasets have been used to evaluate graph pooling methods, such as the MalNet-Tiny (Freitas et al. 2011) dataset, a subset of MalNet (Freitas et al. 2021), a large-scale cybersecurity image database, consisting of function call graphs (FCGs) obtained from Android APKs for predicting software types.",
    "The diversity and uniqueness of these datasets provide rich resources for evaluating graph neural network methods and help promote the further development of GNN research.",
    "Graph data augmentation is the process of modifying or generating new data objects on the graph to increase the diversity of the training set, thus improving the performance and generalization of the model."
  ]
}